Hey, where's Steve? And the pizzas?

15:57.356 --> 16:00.450
- He has forsaken me.
- [Thunderclap ]

16:00.559 --> 16:03.687
I was supposed to be his messenger,
not Roger!

16:03.796 --> 16:07.664
How could he abandon me
after delivering such wisdom? [ Sobs ]

16:07.766 --> 16:11.532
In 30 minutes or less!
[ Crying ]

16:15.674 --> 16:19.269
Hi there. I'm dining with a beautiful woman
somewhere in this restaurant.

16:19.378 --> 16:22.905
Could you ask me to discreetly excuse myself
so I can have a word with me?

16:23.015 --> 16:26.314
I do not understand.
You left 1 5 minutes ago with yourwife.

16:26.418 --> 16:28.386
- Oh, crap! Where'd I go?
- The dance.

16:28.487 --> 16:30.751
The dance? But Betty Sue is there!

16:30.856 --> 16:34.121
What if she sees Francine with me
and tells her I was just there with her?

16:34.226 --> 16:38.162
- [ Clears Throat ]
- You want a tip? Don't wear so much cologne. Ha!

16:40.399 --> 16:43.835
Send them back. Send them all back.

16:43.936 --> 16:46.632
##[Rock]

16:48.507 --> 16:51.908
They say ifyou play it backwards...

16:52.011 --> 16:54.502
you can hear the voice of a dead kid.

16:54.613 --> 16:58.344
Whoa! Wait, how doyou
play Monopoly backwards?

16:58.450 --> 17:00.418
- [Doorbell Rings ]
- [Pounding On Door]

17:00.519 --> 17:02.419
Oh, mein Gott! Oh, mein Gott!

17:02.521 --> 17:04.421
Klaus, cool it!
You're freaking out!

17:04.522 --> 17:06.684
It's the cops!
Quick, flush me down the toilet!

17:06.791 --> 17:09.056
Hayley, let me in!

17:09.161 --> 17:12.561
I was led astray by a false prophet
and I forgot my keys!

17:16.068 --> 17:19.265
Do you know what you've done?
You got Mitch fired!

17:19.371 --> 17:21.339
Why, Steve, why?

17:21.440 --> 17:23.407
Because he chose you over me.

17:23.509 --> 17:26.672
Steve, the truth I offer
isn't personal-pan-sized.

17:26.779 --> 17:30.442
I bring extra-large wisdom
to your door, properly sliced...

17:30.549 --> 17:32.540
that's enough for all mankind.

17:32.651 --> 17:35.916
[ Gasps ]
You didn't fail me.

17:36.021 --> 17:37.955
I failed you.

17:38.057 --> 17:41.322
And I was canned foryour sins.
But I forgiveyou.

17:41.427 --> 17:43.987
Wait, Mitch! Don't go!

17:44.096 --> 17:46.564
I needanotherslice oftruth!

17:47.633 --> 17:50.193
Oh, my God! He's gone.

17:50.302 --> 17:54.432
Yes, he is, Roger. But I have a feeling
he'll be back in three days.

17:54.540 --> 17:56.974
Ah, your faith is so inspiring.

17:57.076 --> 18:00.068
No. I mean, he's got to move his car
for street-sweeping.

18:00.179 --> 18:03.637
## [Dance ]

18:05.150 --> 18:07.118
Why doyou keep looking around?

18:07.219 --> 18:09.744
I'm not! How 'bout some punch?

18:11.490 --> 18:14.220
- Stan!
- Huh! Where?

18:14.326 --> 18:18.285
Get out here, you jerk!
You abandoned me at my own reunion!

18:18.397 --> 18:21.230
Abandoned you?
Oh, thank God! He's not here.

18:21.333 --> 18:25.235
[ Slurring Words ]
I've never been treated so bad mywhole life!

18:25.337 --> 18:30.297
You're filth!
You're a horrible, terrible, horrible person!

18:30.409 --> 18:32.741
You know,
you're a very attractive man.

18:32.845 --> 18:34.813
- Excuse me?
- You heard me.

18:34.913 --> 18:37.882
You're a son of a bitch,
and now I'm gonna kiss you!

18:37.983 --> 18:40.952
- [ Moaning ]
- Stan, what areyou doing?

18:41.053 --> 18:43.453
Uh, Francine, I can explain.

18:43.555 --> 18:46.820
- Francine!
- Stan! Stan?

18:48.227 --> 18:50.718
[ Groans ]

18:50.829 --> 18:53.127
There's four ofyou? That's it.

18:53.232 --> 18:55.496
I've had too much punch.
I'm driving home.

18:55.601 --> 18:57.398
- Okay, bye.
- Seeya.

18:57.503 --> 19:02.497
No one's gonna stop me?
Well, go to hell! I hateyou all!

19:02.608 --> 19:05.236
It's been fun seeing everybody.

19:06.411 --> 19:08.606
What the hell is going on here?

19:08.714 --> 19:12.445
This is, uh-
This is Bill, my C.I.A. double.

19:12.551 --> 19:14.712
- You have a double?
- Yeah.

19:14.820 --> 19:17.653
Sometimes we need decoys
for dangerous missions...

19:17.756 --> 19:20.884
oryour parents' anniversary
or Steve's baptism.

19:20.993 --> 19:23.985
You let me throw myself
at a complete stranger?

19:24.096 --> 19:26.064
Not a complete stranger.

19:26.165 --> 19:29.259
We took that cooking class together.

19:29.368 --> 19:33.327
Look, I only did this 'cause I wanted to go
to the dance with the homecoming queen...

19:33.438 --> 19:35.406
and I didn't wantyou to be mad.

19:35.507 --> 19:39.136
That is so thoughtful. Come here.

19:41.246 --> 19:43.874
Now say good-bye
toyour kneecaps, Stan!

19:43.982 --> 19:48.942
Honey, I knowyou're upset, but I also know
you'd nevershoot an innocent man!

19:51.990 --> 19:54.584
- Damn it! Which one ofyou is Stan?
- [ Both ] He is!

19:54.693 --> 19:56.558
Fine with me.
I'll just shoot you both.

19:56.662 --> 19:59.995
Okay, okay. This has gone on long enough.
[ Sighs ]

20:00.098 --> 20:02.225
Francine, I've been a fool.

20:02.334 --> 20:05.861
All this time I thought I was special
because I married the homecoming queen.

20:05.971 --> 20:09.737
But turns out I was special
because I married you...

20:09.841 --> 20:12.309
not because of some stupid crown.

20:12.411 --> 20:15.869
Oh, I'm so sorry, honey.
I loveyou so much.

20:15.981 --> 20:20.543
Nice try, Bill. Stan would never
say anything that sweet.

20:20.652 --> 20:23.177
Ow! What the hell, you crazy bitch?

20:23.288 --> 20:25.381
Hey, Bill. Come on.
That's mywife, man.

20:26.792 --> 20:30.387
Stan, did you really mean
whatyou said back there?

20:30.495 --> 20:32.463
You'd better believe it, kiddo!

20:32.564 --> 20:36.500
- This is a magical night!
- Mwah!

20:36.602 --> 20:39.070
I don't thinkwe can save the leg!

20:39.171 --> 20:41.366
Oh, no! Oh, God!

20:42.741 --> 20:46.199
